headline: Is DoorDash (DASH) Using WWE and UFC To Deepen Its Grip On Young Consumers?
summary: In November 2025, TKO Group Holdings, Inc. and DoorDash announced an official partnership connecting the delivery platform with WWE and UFC fans through prominent placements at live events, broadcasts, and across their large global social media channels. By tapping into WWE and UFC’s combined audience of more than 1.00 billion young and diverse fans worldwide, DoorDash is positioning its brand directly in front of hard-to-reach 18–34-year-olds and a substantial female fan base. headline: Why The Narrative Around DoorDash Is Shifting Amid Fresh Analyst Updates And New Risks
summary: DoorDash's narrative on Wall Street has shifted subtly but meaningfully, with the Consensus Analyst Price Target nudging higher from $275.20 to $276.17 as analysts factor in stronger core marketplace momentum and improving revenue visibility. Slight upticks in the discount rate and revenue growth forecasts signal that while the risk profile is being reassessed, confidence in the company’s ability to translate expanding gross order value into durable top line strength remains intact.
